{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Lv2qmVdt6cPG8TN7jLVnqV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017zNB52C48ME9FtFyGtbFdk","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Apply corrections to Excel workbook","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"Apply corrections to the Excel workbook at C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\n\nUse openpyxl to make ONLY the following targeted cell changes in the \"Vendor Analysis Assessment\" sheet. Do NOT rebuild the sheet or change anything else. Just update these specific cells:\n\n1. Row 154, Column B (Department): Change \"Finance\" → \"M&A\"\n   (Houlihan Lokey Advisors, LLC — Investment banking advisory is M&A work, not routine Finance)\n\n2. Row 168, Column B (Department): Change \"M&A\" → \"G&A\"\n   (Info Edge India Limited / Naukri.com — This is a job portal for talent acquisition/recruiting, completely wrong to tag as M&A)\n\n3. Row 201, Column B (Department): Change \"Finance\" → \"M&A\"\n   (Livingstone — Description explicitly says \"M&A advisory and investment banking services\")\n\n4. Row 291, Column B (Department): Change \"Finance\" → \"M&A\"\n   (RSM UK Corporate Finance LLP — Description explicitly says \"M&A advisory and corporate finance services\")\n\n5. Row 316, Column B (Department): Change \"Finance\" → \"M&A\"\n   (SS&C Intralinks Inc — Virtual data rooms are M&A tools, description says \"Virtual data room for M&A and deal management\")\n\n6. Row 229, Column E (Suggestion): Change \"Optimize\" → \"Consolidate\"\n   (Navan, Inc — This is the same vendor as Navan (TripActions Inc) in row 228. Both being \"Optimize\" violates the rule that duplicate vendor entries must have at least one as Consolidate. The larger entity ($357K, row 228) stays Optimize; this smaller entity ($57K) becomes Consolidate.)\n\nHere is the Python code to run:\n\n```python\nimport openpyxl\nfrom copy import copy\n\nfilepath = r'C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx'\n\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(filepath)\nws = wb['Vendor Analysis Assessment']\n\n# Verify current values before changing\ncorrections = [\n    (154, 2, \"Finance\", \"M&A\", \"Houlihan Lokey - dept\"),\n    (168, 2, \"M&A\", \"G&A\", \"Info Edge India - dept\"),\n    (201, 2, \"Finance\", \"M&A\", \"Livingstone - dept\"),\n    (291, 2, \"Finance\", \"M&A\", \"RSM UK - dept\"),\n    (316, 2, \"Finance\", \"M&A\", \"SS&C Intralinks - dept\"),\n    (229, 5, \"Optimize\", \"Consolidate\", \"Navan Inc - suggestion\"),\n]\n\nfor row, col, expected, new_val, label in corrections:\n    current = ws.cell(row=row, column=col).value\n    print(f\"Row {row}, Col {col} ({label}): current='{current}', expected='{expected}'\")\n    if current == expected:\n        ws.cell(row=row, column=col).value = new_val\n        print(f\"  -> Updated to '{new_val}'\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"  WARNING: Expected '{expected}' but found '{current}' — skipping\")\n\nwb.save(filepath)\nprint(\"\\nFile saved successfully.\")\n\n# Verify the changes\nwb2 = openpyxl.load_workbook(filepath, data_only=True)\nws2 = wb2['Vendor Analysis Assessment']\nprint(\"\\nVerification:\")\nfor row, col, expected, new_val, label in corrections:\n    val = ws2.cell(row=row, column=col).value\n    print(f\"  Row {row}, Col {col} ({label}): '{val}' — {'OK' if val == new_val else 'MISMATCH'}\")\n```\n\nRun this and report all output including verification results."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25736,"cache_read_input_tokens":6212,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":25736,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"89f939ac-99b7-4385-90